Description: A warrior walking to right under a gateway in Egypt, carrying an animal skin over his shoulder and shield on a lance, and a young man's cut-off head in his hand, accompanied by another warrior; a little boy, wearing animal skin around his waist, covering his eyes, turned towards a black woman, standing at right, wearing a large dagger in her belt; proof illustration to an unidentified publication; after R Caton Woodville. Wood-engraving on thin paper
Producer name: Print made by: Edward J Whymper
